  "texts": [
    "They work by encoding input data into a compressed representation, and then decoding this representation back into the original format.",
    "The aim is to minimize the difference between the original input and the reconstruction, often using a loss function that measures this difference.",
    "In the context of your unsupervised machine translation model, the autoencoder is used to learn language models for Egyptian Arabic and Standard Arabic.",
    "The encoder part of the autoencoder takes a noisy sentence as input and encodes it into a latent space.",
    "The decoder part then attempts to reconstruct the original sentence from this latent representation."
